{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27540f27-27b5-451a-9304-465f900ffbf3","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob — `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n**Impact: HIGH.** `**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree on every evaluation. This is the single most expensive evaluation pattern. As the repo grows, evaluation time grows linearly (or worse) with file count. Use an explicit, narrow glob (e.g., `*.txt`) or list specific files.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n**Impact: MEDIUM.** Property functions that perform file I/O execute during evaluation, not build. This blocks the evaluation phase with disk reads and cannot be cached by MSBuild's evaluation cache. Move this to a build-time target using `ReadLinesFromFile` or a custom task instead.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deeply chained `<Import>` files (3 levels deep)\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\n**Impact: LOW-MEDIUM.** Each import requires MSBuild to locate, open, parse, and evaluate another XML file. Three levels is manageable, but this pattern doesn't scale — in real projects it can balloon. Flatten where possible or consolidate into a single `.props` file.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (priority order)\n\n| # | Pattern | Fix |\n|---|---------|-----|\n| 1 | `**\\*.*` recursive glob | Narrow the glob or list files explicitly |\n| 2 | `File::ReadAllText` in property | Move to a build-time target |\n| 3 | 3-level import chain | Flatten into fewer imports |\n\nIssues 1 and 2 are the most impactful — they introduce disk I/O directly into the evaluation phase, which runs before any build target and cannot be parallelized.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c5059ee7-10e4-4e0b-bbed-68ed1031b85f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project.","outputTokens":551,"requestId":"040D:30E8DC:61E110E:6AB4FB7:69F01084"},"id":"4b44d112-0107-4d9a-93f9-67587429fe84","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:42:41.432Z","parentId":"6470ce58-f089-4b5f-b07c-2ad30b593350"}
